import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data['year'] = data['year'].dt.year
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='people', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of people by year?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.barplot(x="age", y="people", data=data, color='b')
    ax.set(xlabel='Age', ylabel='People')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of people by age?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('sex').sum().reset_index()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax.pie(data['people'], labels=data['sex'], autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=90, colors=['#ff9999','#66b3ff'])
    ax.axis('equal')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of people by sex?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data_pivot = data.pivot("age", "year", "people")
    sns.heatmap(data_pivot, cmap="YlGnBu")
    plt.title("What is the trend of people by age and year?", wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby(['age', 'sex'])['people'].sum().reset_index()
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.barplot(x="age", y="people", hue="sex", data=data)
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of people by age and sex?', wrap=True)
    ax.set_xlabel('Age')
    ax.set_ylabel('People')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
